Many people attended the sombre funeral of the 18-year-old Ndivhudza Mahosi at Tshikhwarani on Saturday.She was killed in a taxi accident at Muduluni last Monday.The school&acute;s principal, Mr Khathutshelo Badugela, said the incident had left many learners traumatized and it would take some time and &quot;specialized counselling for them to recover fully.&quot;Mr Maanda Mulaudzi, a representative of the family, said that the family members were &quot;still in shock after the untimely death&quot;. The family agreed that the death of the child&nbsp;was a great loss to them, the school and the community.